<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/571970-this-question-is-about-the-bbc-miniseries">this question is about the BBC miniseries portrayal of Sugar. What&#39;s up with her unhealthiness; the pasty skin, skin with red itchy patches, and esp the white lips. Did the novel say anything about it, perhaps she had TB?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_571970'><a id="like_count_community_question_571970" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/571970?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F40200.The_Crimson_Petal_and_the_White">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/571970-this-question-is-about-the-bbc-miniseries">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/571970-this-question-is-about-the-bbc-miniseries">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8825504-dianne-bartolotta"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_100x100-6433b08cbe793211f55e184d39e84c4d.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8825504-dianne-bartolotta">Dianne Bartolotta</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">The novel refers to it often. She had psoriasis and it bothered her constantly. Her lips were always peeling and she often pulled the skin off or worr<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">The novel refers to it often. She had psoriasis and it bothered her constantly. Her lips were always peeling and she often pulled the skin off or worried the skin with her teeth. No illness, just a skin condition. Redheads often have skin sensitivities. William sold a face cream that she used when he would give it to her for the patches. I didn't know it was a miniseries and will have to try and find it in the US.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
